title: Bachelor of Science Degree in Computer Science
desc: Having transferred from Dakota County Technical College, I had enrolled at Rasmussen University to pursue further education and a Bachelor's Degree. I was taught more advanced concepts such as Big Data, Development Cycles, Deployment Pipelines, Full-Stack Development, and their real-world applications to industries worldwide.

title: Associate of Applied Science Degree in Software Development
desc: I had enrolled at Dakota County Technical College to further explore my passion for utilizing technology. The coursework has taught me valuable facets of developing enterprise-level technologies, such as Databases, Coding Practices, Debugging, and more.

title: Simley High School Graduate

desc: During my time at Simley High School, I had taken a variety of honors classes in addition to AP courses involving Calculus and Computer Science.
